<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-10T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-10T10:00:00-05:00" n="356" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d356">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/176: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-10T15:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">October 10,
                                        1922—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7:43
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>451. Department’s 297 September 29, 5 p.m. Foreign Office informs me that
                            the British High Commissioner at Constantinople and Minister at Athens
                            are being instructed to urge local representatives of British relief
                            societies to cooperate to the fullest possible extent with the American
                            relief organizations concerned.</p>
                        <p>Above repeated to Constantinople and Athens.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>